title: For Sale:  CIA VZ2008 (VZ58) w/ fixed stock, 5 mags and original bayonet 7.62x39 (+ 100rds free)
postcontent:
I have for sale my Century Arms VZ2008. I bought it new, fired 90-100 rounds total but 7.62x39 just isn't my thing I guess... I'd rather start another AR build for the money.

If you're unfamiliar with this rifle it's basically a VZ58 with a brand new U.S. made receiver and barrel. All other parts such as the furniture are Czech milsurp but are in excellent condition.

Includes the 5 magazines and bayonet which the rifle originally came with.

Changes I made to the rifle:

1. Stock: These come from the factory with a horrible side folding wire stock which I replaced with the original fixed stock which matches the rest of the furniture. The stock was ordered directly from the Czech Republic where they store a lot of their old military surplus equipment.
2. Trigger: This came with a trigger somewhere in the 12 pound range, I don't know for sure because it was over what my scale could read. I followed a guide to lighten the trigger by removing one of the two leaf springs that are not necessary for operation. This is shown in one of the photos. The trigger is now a consistent 5.5 pound pull on my scale.

I fired in total around 90-100 rounds through this rifle (with the improved trigger) and function is flawless. You'll find online people are saying they're able to lighten their triggers further but you risk function issues if you lighten it past what I have done.

$500 price is firm

Contact me through armslist or text 772696zerofourninezero

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Glock 19
postcontent:
Is it me, or has there been an increase in the number of scammers, dishonest, and unrealistic people posting on Armslist recently?  I say this because there are a number of people who attempt to sell there firearms for more than they are going for new.  This tells me that they are either dishonest or they are trying to attract people who are not allowed to buy firearms legally.  Additionally, there seems to be a lapse in clarity about why this site exists.  Well let me spell it out for those who think this site is an extension of craigslist.  In other words, THIS SITE IS FOR THOSE WHO WANT TO SELL OR TRADE GUNS AND GUN RELATED ITEMS!  Therefore, it should be pointed out that 99% of us are really not interested in trading our firearms for TV's, computers, lawnmowers, and rusty old tools.  Don't get me wrong, some of these posts are amusing, however, if I want to be amused i will watch the recents skits SNL has done on Obama.  Now I'm sure some of you will take offense to some of the things that I have said. I certainly expect that, but it should be pointed out that I am merely exercising the constitutional rights that were bestowed on me by the founding fathers of this great country. God bless all of you! Finally, I hope you have a happy Thanksgiving and a Merry Christmas.
Trusty Shellback
